OL,3,CSurprise fall in inflation eases
OL,4,Cpressure on the chancellor, for now
OL,6,FThe companies that will be
OL,7,Fdisproportionally affected by the
OL,8,Fbudget changes are largely employers,
OL,9,Foften operating in competitive sectors
OL,10,Fthat don't make huge profits.
OL,12,FIn many cases, they are restaurants,
OL,13,Fhotels, pubs and retailers and they
OL,14,Fwill variously respond by cutting
OL,15,Fjobs, trimming wage growth, going out
OL,16,Fof business and, where possible,
OL,17,Fincreasing their prices.
