OL,3,CSurprise fall in inflation eases
OL,4,Cpressure on the chancellor, for now
OL,6,FThe extent to which companies will do
OL,7,Fthese things isn't yet clear, which is
OL,8,Fa reason for the Bank of England to
OL,9,Ftread carefully going forward but the
OL,10,Fprobability of an interest rate cut
OL,11,Fnext month has just got higher.
OL,13,FThe headline rate of inflation is
OL,14,Fforecast to rise again in the coming
OL,15,Fmonths, perhaps above 3%, but there is
OL,16,Freason to believe that what the Bank
OL,17,Fof England would call the "underlying
OL,18,Finflationary pressure" - the inflation
OL,19,Fit can attempt to influence - is
OL,20,Ffading.
